title: Canaveral National Seashore: Park Home
body: Reflect on the Real Florida  Since ancient times, this barrier island has provided sanctuary to both people and wildlife. Many threatened animals find refuge here, including sea turtles who nest on its shores. Like Indians and early settlers, you too can find tranquility. Swim in the ocean. Fish in the lagoon. Stroll down a wooded trail. Or reflect on the longest expanse of pristine shore in Florida - the way it used to be.              Stop by the Visitor Center first...   Stop by the visitor center for park information & a current schedule of monthly interpretive program offerings...
